<taxonomicName authority="Walsingham, 1907" authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1907" box="[461,637,1926,1951]" class="Insecta" family="Blastobasidae" genus="Hypatopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="136" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rudis">
<emphasis box="[461,637,1926,1951]" italics="true" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">Hypatopa rudis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from one collecting site in northwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[1210,1333,1926,1950]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
in a dryforest region southwest of the Cordillera de Guanacaste.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="136.[151,1437,882,2022]" box="[199,1171,1998,2022]" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">
