<taxonomicName authority="Walsingham, 1907" authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1907" box="[563,621,1998,2022]" class="Insecta" family="Blastobasidae" genus="Hypatopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="136" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rudis">
<emphasis box="[563,621,1998,2022]" italics="true" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">rudis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is derived from the Latin meaning, a small stick.
</paragraph>
